The most straightforward sensitivity to light new states occur in models where such states can be thermally populated and therefore contribute, at a considerable level, to Universe’s energy balance, affecting the expansion rate of the Universe. As a consequence, the timing of nuclear reactions, and elemental yield of helium and deuterium can be altered. In addition, the presence of an extra component to radiation-like energy density can be severely constrained by the CMB observable Neff\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
