				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {keV}_{{ee}}$$\end{document}.7

Three Xe-based experiments have released over the last years the strongest constraints on WIMP-nucleus interaction above 6 GeV: XENON1T at LNGS [287], LUX at the Sanford Underground Research Facility (SURF) in US [288] and PANDAX-II at Jinping Underground Laboratory in China [289, 290]. Considering only the S2 signal, above 0.4 keVee\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
