NA64 is specially designed as a hermetic general purpose detector to search for dark sector physics in missing energy events from high-energy electron and muon scattering off nuclei in an active dump. The main aim of the NA64 experiment (North Area experiment 64) at the CERN SPS is the detection of Light Dark Matter (LDM) motivated by freeze-out DM models. The method of the search can be illustrated by considering, as an example, the search for the vector mediator, e.g. the dark photon A′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
