A more ambitious extrapolation of this experimental technique is conceivable, for example, as a byproduct of a possible future production of a large number of dipoles like the one needed for the Future Circular Collider (FCC). This is the idea behind JURA, a long-term possibility discussed in the Physics Beyond Colliders study group [506]. JURA contemplates a magnetic length of almost 1 km, and would suppose a further step in sensitivity of more than one order of magnitude in gaγ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
