Before concluding this section, let us mention that a DM axion with keV mass (or higher) and with sufficiently strong coupling to electrons would show up in low background massive detectors developed for WIMP searches [127, 568, 569], as a non-identified peak at an energy equal to the mass, by virtue of the axioelectric effect. The recent XENON1T low-energy electronic recoil event excess [108] could be interpreted as such a signal, with a favoured value for mA∼2.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
