				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\varLambda $$\end{document}, like e.g. the R-axion (pNGB of the broken R-symmetry in SUSY) [638], pseudoscalar states in Higgs compositeness models (from the broken U(1) symmetry acting on all underlying fermions of the theory) [639], or in cosmic inflation [640];
generic pseudoscalar bosons that appear e.g. in extended Higgs sectors [641], in phenomenological realizations of string theory [642], in models where they contribute to lepton dipole moments (thereby solving the (g-2)μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
