The latter fact is, to date, the only firmly established piece of evidence for the existence of physics beyond the minimal SM that has been observed in the laboratory. Hence, studying neutrino masses and mixings may provide a key how the SM should be embedded in a more fundamental theory of nature. In particular, questions of interest are the mass puzzle and the flavour puzzle, i.e., the questions why their masses mi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
