MicroBooNE: the MicroBooNE detector [938] started data taking with the Booster Neutrino Beam (BNB, 8 GeV proton beam, Fermilab, USA) in 2015, making it the first fully operational detector of the three liquid-Argon time projection chambers comprising the Short-Baseline Neutrino Program (SBN) [939]. The SBN program aims to address the short-baseline anomalies observed by the MiniBooNE and LSND collaborations. In addition to the studies of the effects of light eV-scale sterile neutrinos, the energy range of the BNB makes possible to extend the sensitivity of the detectors to the production and decay of HNLs with masses of O(100)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
