SBN program: the SBN [939] project is based on three detectors placed in the BNB at different (short) baseline distances: SBND at 110 m from the target, MicroBooNE at 470 m and ICARUS at 600 m. All three detectors utilize LArTPC technology with powerful event reconstruction capabilities allowing for a significantly improved understanding of background processes compared to predecessor technologies. With this design, SBN has been shown to be able to extend the current bounds on light oscillating sterile neutrinos, thoroughly exploring the eV-scale sterile neutrino mass region, whilst also pursuing many other physics goals including a search for heavy neutral leptons [954]. It is expected that the SBN program can extend existing bounds on well constrained channels such as N→νℓ+ℓ-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
