LHCb is a forward spectrometer whose special features are particularly useful for the detection of light FIPs. Examples of these features include an advanced vertexing, and excellent momentum resolution and particle identification (PID). Furthermore, the LHCb trigger is capable of triggering on very soft objects compared to other LHC experiments [971]. This will be reinforced after the current upgrade of the detector, when this will be readout at every LHC bunch-crossing, allowing a trigger fully-based on software, which is very convenient to detect FIPs. A very important aspect of this new trigger will be the use of GPUs [972], which will allow maintaining soft pT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
